content:
What is the JavaScript code to generate a random flower name from an array of flower names, along with its unique meaning or cultural significance attached to it?
Here's an example array of flower names and their meanings:
const flowers = [
  {name: "Rose", meaning: "love and passion"},
  {name: "Lily", meaning: "purity and innocence"},
  {name: "Cherry Blossom", meaning: "transience and beauty"},
  {name: "Lotus", meaning: "enlightenment and rebirth"}
];
What code can be used to randomly select a flower from this array and display its name and meaning on the page?
